article.description: — Trevian Tennyson scored 20 points to lead Texas A&M Corpus Christi to an 80-64 victory over Incarnate Word on Saturday.
article.headline: Texas A&M-Corpus Christi beats Incarnate Word 80-64
article.linkText: Texas A&M-Corpus Christi beats Incarnate Word 80-64
article.story: CORPUS CHRISTI, Texas -- — Trevian Tennyson scored 20 points to lead Texas A&M Corpus Christi to an 80-64 victory over Incarnate Word on Saturday. Tennyson was 7 of 9 from the floor and made four 3-pointers. Isaac Mushila added 13 points and Terrion Murdix had 12 for Texas A&M-CC (14-4, 1-0 Southland Conference), which has won four of its last five games. RJ Glasper scored 28 points to lead Incarnate Word (4-14, 0-1). Incarnate Word host Houston Baptist on Thursday. Texas A&M-CC will look to win its third straight, hosting McNeese on Thursday. ------
